ol.li: Initial Redirection: First few bytes of original function are replaced with a jump to trampoline
State Preservation: Trampoline saves all CPU registers to stack
Hook Execution: Custom monitoring/analysis function is called
State Restoration: Original register values are restored
Original Prologue: Displaced instructions from original function are executed
Return to Normal: Execution continues in original function body

div.p: Key Property: The trampoline is transparent - original function behavior is preserved.
